{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3416156,"name":"","username":"pathal","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/p/edb3f5/{size}.png","created_at":"2024-08-17T18:25:12.805Z","cooked":"<p>Hi all, our <span class="abbreviation">FRC<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="FIRST Robotics Competition"></template></span> team is looking to run a more sophisticated vision pipeline next year, and I’m trying to set up the build system and environment for them early.</p>
<p>I’ve found a cmake / intellisense issue where wpilib is hijacking the opencv namespace, despite that all we’re using from it is ntcore and building with cmake.</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">#include &lt;ntcore_cpp.h&gt;
#include &lt;networktables/NetworkTable.h&gt;
#include &lt;networktables/DoubleTopic.h&gt;
#include &lt;networktables/NetworkTableInstance.h&gt;
...
cv::Mat a = cv::imread(fpath);
</code></pre>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">name followed by '::' must be a class or namespace name
namespace wpi::cv
</code></pre>
<p>The code builds and runs correctly, and right-click open document on the opencv headers link to the /usr/local/ install location. So intellisense knows that these files exist. The VSCode includepath is only:</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">"/usr/local/include",
"/usr/local/include/opencv4",
"${workspaceFolder}/build/_deps/wpilib-src/ntcore/**",
"${workspaceFolder}/build/_deps/wpilib-src/wpiutil/**"
</code></pre>
<p>And searching wpilib for <code>namespace cv</code> only returns hits in cscore and cameraserver, neither of which we’re linking with. So it appears that something with the dependency tree is causing intellisense to pick up on the wrong namespace in (seemingly) unrelated files.</p>
<p>Converting our <code>cv::Mat a = cv::imread("");</code> to <code>wpi::cv::Mat a = wpi::cv::imread("");</code> causes intellisense to understand the linkage and properly render the docstrings… but then we can’t build.</p>
<p>If anyone has any thoughts or advice on how to fix this without tediously picking individual headers to link, we’d love to hear it.</p>","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"posts_count":4,"updated_at":"2024-08-17T18:25:12.805Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":42,"reads":70,"readers_count":69,"score":224.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":469958,"topic_slug":"c-opencv-namespace-intellisense-errors","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":67512,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/c-opencv-namespace-intellisense-errors/469958/1","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":true,"can_vote":false},{"id":3416226,"name":"Peter Johnson","username":"Peter_Johnson","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/peter_johnson/{size}/10417_2.png","created_at":"2024-08-18T02:47:15.313Z","cooked":"<p>Sounds like an Intellisense bug.  I don’t think we can do anything about it.  I personally don’t use the Microsoft C++ extension intellisense, but use clangd instead, which seems to be more robust.</p>","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"posts_count":4,"updated_at":"2024-08-18T02:47:15.313Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":43,"readers_count":42,"score":13.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":469958,"topic_slug":"c-opencv-namespace-intellisens